HEADWORD: Subnormal
<hw>Sub*nor"mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>
<def>That part of the axis of a curved line which is intercepted between
the ordinate and the normal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

